As no complete flowers were available in herbarium material, description of floral characters is based in part on field observations of a single living flower at distance. The collector, D. Sabatier, has informed us that an attempt to collect that flower which was high up in a large tree and out of reach had failed. Sabatier (pers. comm.) notices 5 scars per whorl on the receptacle (compare 
Figure 3A
) implying that we have a 5-merous flower here! This definitely requires confirmation from further collections, though.
